According to the Glenvista Community Policing Forum, a truck &#8220;transporting cool drinks broke down on the N12 West Motorway between Voortrekker and Comaro Road off-ramps&#8221; and they then &#8220;got calls that the truck was being looted&#8221;. &#8220;People were pulling off in droves and stealing stock from the truck. Even a Sasko delivery truck stopped and loaded some stolen stock.&#8221; The page alleged that on Friday the &#8220;looters were so many that they even caused a traffic jam on the Motorway&#8221;. They wrote that they were publishing the photos in the hope that the thieves would be successfully apprehended. Take a look in the full post below. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.